The paper deals with computational complexity in the context of strategic behavior in judgment aggregation, which involves combining individual judgments into a collective decision. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of determining whether certain outcomes can be achieved through strategic behavior, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
